<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2262] LogSegmentSize validation should be consistent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2262</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In KafkaConfig, we have the following constraint on LogSegmentBytes&lt;br/&gt;
      .define(LogSegmentBytesProp, INT, Defaults.LogSegmentBytes, atLeast(Message.MinHeaderSize), HIGH, LogSegmentBytesDoc)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, at LogConfig level, the constraint is a bit different. We should make it to be the same as in KafkaConfig.&lt;br/&gt;
      .define(SegmentBytesProp, INT, Defaults.SegmentSize, atLeast(0), MEDIUM, SegmentSizeDoc)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
